boolean isIpBanned(String ip) {
    String line = null;
    try {
        reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("data/bannedips.txt"));
        while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {
            if (line.equals(ip)) {
                System.out.println("Client rejected from "+ip);
                return true;
            }
        }
    } catch(Exception e){}
    return false;
}This boolean is very simple to understand. But if you have trouble(s) understanding, I will explain it to you. What it does is it reads the 'bannedips.txt' file and checks for the ip not to equal the String in the parameters of this boolean. If it does equal, it will return true and print a message onto the console, and if not it will return false. Now, we're going to call this boolean.</blockquote>


